Italy to ‘Translate’ French Anti-Takeover Rules, Ansa Reports

-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 
2011-03-27T14:33:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/italy-to-translate-french-anti-takeover-rules-ansa-reports.html
Italy  intends to present to Europe
France’s rules “translated into Italian” on takeovers, Italian
news agency Ansa reported today, citing Finance Minister Giulio
Tremonti.  Tremonti was referring to anti-takeover rules that may be
used for  Parmalat SpA (PLT) , Italy’s biggest dairy company, Ansa said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  